        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/{size}/326_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-22T21:45:02.271Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This topic came up during a meeting.  It was agreed that best effort maintaining bazel should be a low maintenance burden, and as long as we have sufficiently clear documentation describing its level of support, it shouldn\u2019t cause new developer confusion.  Thus, no one seemed opposed, so it seems you\u2019re welcome to have bazel support for as long as you have an interest in maintaining it.</p>\n<p>I\u2019ll comb through your PR for bazel in more detail once all the header changes have dropped out, and I\u2019ll go put some thought into how FDB fits into bazel\u2019s opinionated view of the world.</p>",
